#Text=The New Orleans Pelicans ( 34 - 29 ) defeated the Memphis Grizzlies ( 44 - 18 ) 95 - 89 on Saturday at the Smoothie King Center in New Orleans .

#Text=Coming into this game sitting just one game back from the Oklahoma City Thunder for the final projected playoff seed in the Western Conference standings , the Pelicans pulled off a big win Saturday , bringing themselves to within a half game of the Thunder .

#Text=Despite being down 50 - 38 at half , the Pelicans took off in the third quarter , out - scoring the Grizzlies 33 - 17 to help set themselves up for the six - point victory in front of their home crowd .
#Text=The Pelicans were the superior shooters in this game , going 48 percent from the field , while the Grizzlies finished at just 43 percent .
#Text=The Pelicans were led by the duo of Anthony Davis and Tyreke Evans in this one .
#Text=Evans went 10 - for - 16 from the field and 3 - for - 8 from the three - point line to finish with a team - high of 26 points , to go along with seven rebounds and three steals .
#Text=He struggled to just 11 points on Friday against the Boston Celtics , so it was good to see him rebound with a big performance .
#Text=Davis , on the other hand , finished with 23 points ( 11 - 21 FG , 1 - 1 FT ) , 10 rebounds and five blocked shots in 40 minutes .

#Text=After missing five games in a row with a shoulder injury , the Pelicans are loving what they 're seeing from their superstar , as he 's averaged 30 points , 12 rebounds and 5 blocks in the three games since his return .
#Text=He 's pushed his season averages to 24 points and 10 rebounds on the year .
#Text=Eric Gordon also played a factor in the win , as he posted 16 points ( 4 - 6 FG , 3 - 5 3Pt , 5 - 5 FT ) and six assists in 35 minutes .
#Text=He 's played well of late as well , combining for 36 points and eight assists over his last two games .
#Text=For the Grizzlies , Jeff Green did the bulk of the work offensively .
#Text=He went 8 - for - 18 from the field , but 0 - for - 3 from the three - point line to record 20 points , while adding four rebounds and three assists as well .

#Text=He had shot less than 30 percent in two out of his last three games coming into Saturday , so it was good to see him get things turned around and have a productive showing from the field in this matchup .
#Text=Mike Conley also had a strong showing , finishing with 17 points ( 5 - 9 FG , 3 - 6 3Pt , 4 - 4 FT ) , four rebounds and three assists of his own over 30 minutes .
#Text=He 's been quite inconsistent with his scoring lately , but he was able to put up some decent numbers Saturday .
#Text=With both Zach Randolph and Marc Gasol combining for just 15 points between the two , Beno Udrih was the only other Grizzlies ' player in double figures for points .
#Text=In just 15 minutes off the bench , he posted 11 points ( 4 - 6 FG , 3 - 3 FT ) and four rebounds .
#Text=With a few of their stars struggling in this one , the Grizzlies just were n't able to overcome the Pelicans ' strong play .
#Text=The Pelicans ' next game will be on the road against the Milwaukee Bucks on Monday , while the Grizzlies will travel to Chicago to play the Bulls on Monday .
